The paper is about transfer learning in natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the interaction between computers and human languages. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques and architectures, such as transformers and neural networks, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions benchmarks for tasks such as summarization and text classification, which are related to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
